      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what's wrong and is it safe to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A loud humming noise from your AC unit, with the fan not spinning, could be a sign that the fan motor is failing or there's an issue with the electrical connection. Before you go looking at it, it's important to ensure your safety. If you're not comfortable with electrical work, it's best to call a professional. However, if you're feeling adventurous and have some basic knowledge, you can check a few things yourself.\n\nFirst, make sure the power to the AC unit is turned off at the circuit breaker. This is crucial to avoid any electrical hazards. Once you've done that, you can inspect the fan blades for any obstructions or debris that might be causing the humming noise. Sometimes, a small object can get lodged in the fan, causing it to hum without spinning.\n\nIf the fan blades are clear, you can check the fan motor itself. Look for any visible signs of damage or wear. If you see anything unusual, it's best to call a professional. However, if everything looks fine, you can try to wiggle the fan motor gently to see if it moves. If it doesn't, the motor might be the culprit.\n\nRemember, if you're not confident in your ability to safely inspect and potentially repair the AC unit, it's always best to call",
